Mapfluence Session Notes
Date: 2026-03-18

User workflow preferences
- Commit and push to `main` after completed code changes until the user says otherwise.
- Keep practical, restart-safe notes in this `.mb` file.

Current Hastings map architecture target
- Admin full map: `/:universityId/admin` (Mapfluence edit + AI + planning tools).
- Admin combined stakeholder + technical: `/:universityId/admin/engagement`.
- Public stakeholder engagement: `/:universityId/engagement`.
- Public technical assessment: `/:universityId/technical`.

Latest completed work
- Removed `/:universityId/admin/technical` route.
- Kept technical routes in public shell and restored technical assessment loading there.
- Allowed marker placement in admin engagement map (assessment view), while preventing placement during technical panel view.
- Hid full Mapfluence/space-export/planning/AI blocks from technical-only mode.
- Enabled admin sign-in controls on technical pages for authorized saves.

Latest completed work (follow-up hardening)
- Added explicit route-mode header text in controls so each URL clearly labels its purpose.
- Kept controls toggle available on technical routes (not just admin) for cleaner presentation.
- Added map-view/panel sync: technical panel now auto-opens when entering Technical view with a selected building and closes when leaving Technical view.
- Added route guard cleanup so non-full-admin routes auto-close Mapfluence-only AI/room-edit overlays.
- Added route guard cleanup so planning scenario mode is forced off outside the full admin map.

Latest completed work (technical autosave)
- Added debounced local draft autosave for Technical Assessment edits.
- Drafts are keyed by university + building and restore automatically when reopening that building.
- Added in-panel save state messaging: Unsaved, Saving draft, Draft restored/saved, Saving to cloud, Saved to cloud, and Error.
- Kept cloud save as explicit admin-only action and added non-admin hint that local drafts are still being preserved.

Latest completed work (admin combined workflow)
- Added `Workflow Focus` quick chips in `/admin/engagement`:
  - Stakeholder Focus
  - Technical Focus
- Stakeholder Focus sets assessment view and emphasizes marker/heatmap workflow.
- Technical Focus jumps to technical view and quiets engagement heat/sentiment overlays for cleaner assessment work.

Latest completed work (workflow separation refinement)
- In `/admin/engagement`, workflow options are now `Stakeholder` and `Technical` (renamed from `Assessment`).
- Stakeholder workflow now shows only stakeholder tools (markers/heatmap/sentiment controls).
- Technical workflow now hides stakeholder tools and surfaces only technical assessment behavior.
- Added a stakeholder building-condition toggle in combined mode to enable/disable whole-building stakeholder condition editing panel.
- Prevented stakeholder marker popup from opening on building clicks when building-condition editing is enabled.
- In `/technical`, workflow dropdown now contains only `Technical` (no `Assessment` option).

Latest completed work (panel/visibility cleanup)
- Removed duplicate `Workflow Focus` block and retained workflow switching via the dropdown only.
- In combined mode, building recolor now follows workflow:
  - Stakeholder workflow: multicolor stakeholder condition shading.
  - Technical workflow: blue technical-assessment progress shading after saves.
- Removed stakeholder panel buttons: `Export PNG`, `Presentation Mode`, `Export Clean PNG` (and removed `Export Clean PNG` from presentation quick controls).
- Updated floorplan plain fill to a solid off-white (no transparency bleed-through).

Latest completed work (admin engagement floorplan + panel usability)
- In `/admin/engagement`, switching workflow to `Technical` now unloads any currently loaded floorplan so technical mode starts on campus view.
- Fixed stakeholder marker placement inside loaded floorplans while keeping building-click blocking for whole-building condition edits in campus scope.
- Made the left controls panel scrollable (`max-height` + vertical overflow) so lower sections (including Floorplans) remain reachable when Room Sentiment content is expanded.

Latest completed work (admin marker data tools)
- Added `Admin Data Tools` in `/admin/engagement` Stakeholder workflow.
- Added marker filtering by:
  - building
  - floor
  - room text (number/id/label)
  - marker type
- Added selection workflow for filtered markers (`Select Filtered`, checkbox list, `Clear Selection`).
- Added `Export Filtered CSV` with marker + room-context fields (roomNumber, roomId, roomGuid, revitId, roomLabel).
- Added `Delete Selected` with confirmation and batched cloud deletes, while also handling local-only markers safely.

Latest completed work (technical completion tracking)
- Added `Technical Progress` panel when Technical workflow is active.
- Added per-building completion tracking with:
  - completion percent (`answered fields / total technical fields`)
  - section start count (`x / 3 sections started`)
  - missing section badges (`Codes`, `Engineering`, `Functionality`) when a section has no scores set.
- Added `Jump To Next Incomplete` action to move directly to the next building needing technical input.
- Added click-to-focus rows that select the building, open technical assessment, and zoom to the building footprint.

Latest completed work (admin mode memory)
- Added persisted admin combined preferences (`/admin/engagement`) in local storage keyed by university + user.
- Restores on reload:
  - workflow (`Stakeholder` vs `Technical`)
  - stakeholder scope (`campus` vs `floor`)
  - selected building
  - selected building id
  - selected floor
- Persist/restore is isolated to admin combined mode so public and technical-only routes are unaffected.

Latest completed work (technical progress utilities)
- Added `Incomplete Only` toggle in the Technical Progress panel.
- Added `Export Missing Items CSV` for technical follow-up:
  - building id/name
  - completion percent and answered/total fields
  - missing section list
  - missing field count + field list
- Technical checklist panel now reports `Visible` count and supports filtered review workflows.

Latest completed work (admin marker hard-delete safety)
- Replaced hard delete behavior in `Admin Data Tools` with soft archive behavior:
  - `Archive Selected` now sets marker archive fields instead of deleting records.
  - Archived markers are hidden from normal map marker/heatmap/sentiment workflows by default.
- Added archive visibility + recovery controls:
  - `Show archived markers in filters/list` toggle
  - `Undo Last Archive` one-click restore
- Added archive metadata to filtered CSV export:
  - `IsArchived`, `ArchivedAt`, `ArchivedBy`
- Added active/archived counts in admin tools for quick hygiene checks.

Latest completed work (archived purge + marker attribution correctness)
- Added permanent cleanup action in `Admin Data Tools`:
  - `Permanently Delete Archived` (selected archived markers only)
  - Two-step safety confirmation (`confirm` + type `DELETE`)
  - Deletes from Firestore for cloud markers and removes local-only archived markers from session state.
- Fixed marker attribution in engagement mode so building/floor context is only attached when valid:
  - Campus scope: marker gets `buildingId/buildingName` only when click lands on a building footprint.
  - Floor scope: marker gets `building/floor/room` context only when click lands inside the loaded floorplan geometry.
  - Outside-building clicks no longer inherit the Floorplans panel selection, preventing false `buildingId/buildingName` assignment.

Latest completed work (admin marker unassigned cleanup tools)
- Added quick assignment filters in `Admin Data Tools`:
  - `All Markers`
  - `No Building`
  - `No Floor`
  - `Unassigned`
- Added one-click `Select Unassigned` action (within current filtered set).
- Added summary counters for `No Building`, `No Floor`, and `Unassigned`.
- Added explicit marker list labels for missing assignment:
  - `(No building)`
  - `(No floor)`

Latest completed work (one-click unassigned archive)
- Added `Archive Unassigned` button in `Admin Data Tools`.
- Button archives all currently filtered unassigned markers in one action (no manual checkbox selection required).
- Keeps archive safety behavior:
  - cloud markers are soft-archived (not deleted)
  - local-only markers are archived in session state
  - `Undo Last Archive` restores the archived batch
- Updated quick-filter first chip label to `All Markers` for clarity.

Latest completed work (technical assessment QA hardening - phase 1)
- Fixed technical assessment save race between local draft autosave and cloud save:
  - Cloud save now clears any pending autosave timer before writing.
  - Prevents stale draft writes from reappearing immediately after successful cloud save.
- Hardened technical cloud save payload:
  - Uses Firestore merge writes (`setDoc(..., { merge: true })`) to avoid clobbering unrelated future metadata.
  - Adds `updatedAt` server timestamp on cloud saves.
- Hardened technical save failure behavior:
  - On cloud save failure, the current assessment is immediately persisted to local draft storage.
  - Keeps draft recovery reliable even when cloud save fails mid-session.
- Minor export hygiene:
  - Technical missing-items CSV now revokes blob URLs after download.

Latest completed work (technical assessment QA hardening - phase 2)
- Added legacy-field normalization for technical score data to improve completion tracking accuracy across older saved records.
- Completion tracking now treats common legacy aliases as equivalent to canonical fields (for example: `telecom` -> `telecomm`, `hvac` -> `mechanical`, `codesAccessibility` -> `codesAndAccessibility`).
- Unified technical progress and building-shading logic to use the same normalized scoring computation, preventing mismatches between checklist percentages and blue progress shading.
- Technical assessment panel now normalizes legacy score keys when loading/editing records, so older data opens with correct field values instead of appearing as missing.
